The Memes Collection is focused on the fight for the open metaverse (decentralization, community, self-sovereignty) and spreading this message to many people, many wallets.

It is a collection that is meant to be open and accessible. Edition sizes will generally be large and inexpensive, to spread the word and to avoid gas wars.

We will try to have a good time along the way, make some fun art, do great collabs and just generally have a good time.

For more information visit https://6529.io/collections/the-memes/

metadata.name: Founder Pass #0
metadata.description:
H.E.L.I.X (Hyper Expansive Lifelike Interoperable eXperience) is a high-fidelity metaverse platform built around the core pillars of ultra-realism, true digital ownership, and player-owned economy. 

Initially set in an open-world, 1:1 scale recreation of New York City, players can own and build on land, trade items, play various games, and earn tokens. Every single item in HELIX has finite supply and is represented by an underlying NFT.

Initially set in an open-world, 1:1 scale recreation of New York City, players can own and build on land, trade items, play various games, and earn tokens. Every single item in HELIX has finite supply and is represented by an underlying NFT.

The Founder Pass  is the best way to take full advantage of one of the most immersive Metaverse experiences on the Blockchain. The Founder Pass is 5000 NFTs that grant 3 months early access to play HELIX. Founder Pass holders will be entitled to exclusive airdrops, free land, exclusive designer clothes, supercars, and much more.


Our EA pass holders will become HELIX’s tightly knit “alpha” community and be a pinnacle of the development of our game. Holders have the opportunity to be beta testers and take part in the most elite blockchain gaming community.

metadata.description: In the Outskirts, Wagmi-san hones his craft. Some day perhaps a clash of luck, inspiration, and talent will make him known to the world. That day is not today. A man of honor, he only makes objects for customers who own parent NFTs. His accessories are 1 of 1 digital objects. Life is good. As long as the deliveries stay on schedule. We know what happens when they don’t.

As the House of the World was shattered, the Elemental Houses would rise from its remains. Mighty Champions willing to represent the four Elements: Air, Fire, Earth and Water, claimed their right to fight in the Colosseum Eternal, but the Emperor had other plans. Until now. The Elemental Champions are allowed in the arena once more and the stakes have never been higher.

Gatekeeper: The brutal and stoic cousins of the Keymasters, this race was also cast out when they chose to help Massina to stave off the Darulk invasion. The Gatekeeper’s consciousness lives a few seconds in the future, allowing them to see the moves of their opponents before they even know what they want to do. This has proven very effective to keep intruders out of the Heavens, and as citizens of Massina, even more useful in their path to Ascension and their burning desire to return home.

metadata.description:

Mighty Champions willing to represent the four Elements: Air, Fire, Earth and Water, claimed their right to fight in the Colosseum Eternal, but the Emperor had other plans. Until now. The Elemental Champions are finally allowed in the arena once more and the stakes have never been higher!

Il’gra: “You never know what an Il’gra is thinking. Hell, you don’t even know *if* they’re thinking.” In battle, the Il’gra is known for letting each head suggest its own strategy, and it is impossible to tell which one it will pick. Mix this unpredictability with the fact that the beast is strong enough to crush a Darulk’s skull with one hand and you have one of the Emperor’s favorite gladiators. Their behaviour in the Arena was so erratic, that for two centuries oddsmakers at the Tavern refused to take any bets where Il’gra were concerned.
metadata.name: Elemental #1001

metadata.description:
As the House of the World was shattered, the Elemental Houses would rise from its remains. Mighty Champions willing to represent the four Elements: Air, Fire, Earth and Water, claimed their right to fight in the Colosseum Eternal, but the Emperor had other plans. Until now. The Elemental Champions are finally allowed in the arena once more and the stakes have never been higher!

Saadari: When the City of the Moon was destroyed, the female legionaries of Trib became cursed with an unquenchable thirst for blood and sentenced to walk the planet forever in eternal pain. Having long forgotten their human pasts, the Saadari now willingly participate in the games attempting to satisfy their thirst, or find final peace. Kill or be killed, it's a win/win for them. Their bones and fangs are specially sought after by the Osteomancer to create pieces of armor that can be enchanted with magical properties.
metadata.name: Elemental #1002

metadata.description:
As the House of the World was shattered, the Elemental Houses would rise from its remains. Mighty Champions willing to represent the four Elements: Air, Fire, Earth and Water, claimed their right to fight in the Colosseum Eternal, but the Emperor had other plans. Until now. The Elemental Champions are finally allowed in the arena once more and the stakes have never been higher!

Seris: At home atop the northern mountain ranges, the Seris share a common ancestor with the Vitra, but that is pretty much it. Thunder coursing through their veins instead of blood, Seris are terribly resilient and can focus the energy within their bodies to deliver impossibly powerful attacks, or quickly close off an otherwise deadly wound. Unlike most races whose culture is intertwined with participating in the gladiatorial games, Seris see themselves as superior to the rest and shun those that take part in such frivolous endeavors. As a result, most Seris that you will find in the arena are outcasts with dark pasts. Or perhaps someone that asked too many questions about the immense fortune that the Seris are amassing beneath the mountain.
metadata.name: Elemental #1003

metadata.description:
As the House of the World was shattered, the Elemental Houses would rise from its remains. Mighty Champions willing to represent the four Elements: Air, Fire, Earth and Water, claimed their right to fight in the Colosseum Eternal, but the Emperor had other plans. Until now. The Elemental Champions are finally allowed in the arena once more and the stakes have never been higher!

Keymaster: The Celestials known as Keymasters and Gatekeepers are keepers of secrets: the knowledge of all existences, future, past and present. But they do not always see eye to eye. The Keymasters vowed to remain uninvolved, even as demons spilled out of Hell and ransacked Massina. Finally they relented and helped the Emperor to save the world, but in so doing, were cast out of Heaven. Now they live among mortals. It is said that whoever stares into their forehead will see their best possible life, something that has been known to drive even the wisest of priests insane.

Fenrir: The forests and hills of the west once housed many wonders, including the long lost City of the Moon, where the peaceful Fenrir lived in communion with nature. But then the conquering Darulk came, and along with Saadari mercenaries, burned it all to ash. The ferocious yet noble Fenrir fled to Massina City, where they accommodated to their harsh new reality and became feared Champions of its ruthless gladiatorial games. It is not unusual to hear the howling of the crowd from several miles away whenever a Fenrir enters the arena.

Aos: Six hundred years ago, the priestess of the House of the Arcane came upon a terrible secret. A secret so immense, that it angered both Celestials and the current Emperor, who swiftly punished the women and burned their quarter to the ground. A few nights later, some children that were going through the rubble heard a group of women singing, and to their horror, recognized the priestesses that were vanquished the week before. No longer sworn to the House of Arcane, these women freely walked the streets of the city, protected by the people who saw their return as a sign that they had been wronged. Unwilling to face a revolt, the Emperor pardoned them as long as they were willing to participate in the gladiatorial games. Their opponents would quickly learn that the forbidden knowledge they amassed through their studies was even more dangerous than the sharpest of swords. To this day it is still unknown if they can recall the secret that caused their downfall.

Tribes of Grondal can be found across the planet, and although customs may vary between them, a few things remain the same: their young undergo a brutal procedure whereby the section of the brain that feels fear is cut away, and the left arm burnt to the bone, replaced by a tough metal alloy. Fearless and constantly hungry, they will not stop until everyone in the arena is dead. Even if that also means them.

Gatekeeper: The brutal and stoic cousins of the Keymasters, this race was also cast out when they chose to help Massina to stave off the Darulk invasion. The Gatekeeper’s consciousness lives a few seconds in the future, allowing them to see the moves of their opponents before they even know what they want to do. This has proven very effective to keep intruders out of the Heavens, and as citizens of Massina, even more useful in their path to Ascension and their burning desire to return home.

Their bones and fangs are specially sought after by the Osteomancer to create pieces of armor that can be enchanted with magical properties.

A favorite of the Tavern’s patrons, betting on battles where Whisperers are involved is not for the faint of heart.

Darulk: Whereas the Whisperers snuck into Massina, the Darulk thundered in like a conquering storm. Preferring a violent approach to get whatever they desired, they ruled over vast areas of the planet for thousands of years, until the first Emperor, joined by the Celestials, united all other races against the demons. Feared and revered in the Arena, perhaps the old adage describes them best: “The only way to beat a Darulk… is to be a Darulk.”
